`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Why source-level tests instead of DOM rendering?** This codebase uses `readFileSync` to analyze component source code rather than mounting React components with `@testing-library/react`. This works well here because:
- The components have complex portal/DOM dependencies that are hard to mock in happy-dom
- Structural properties (conditional guards, prop wiring, timing tokens) are stable contracts that don't change with refactors
- Source analysis catches wiring issues that rendering tests might miss (e.g., a prop being passed but never used)

**The `position !== "static"` pattern** (line 136) is a clean exclusion guard — it automatically supports any future CSS position values without needing a whitelist update. This is better than `position === "absolute" || position === "fixed" || ...` which would need maintenance.
